# W5-b HONEST REJECTION: a str-ONLY method called on `bytes` is an honest "type
# `bytes` has no method" CHECK error, never a stub or a rustc E0599 leak. `encode`
# lives on `str` (you *encode* a str, *decode* bytes) and is NOT in the bytes method
# surface, so `b.encode()` rejects. (W5-a used b.upper() here, which is now a REAL
# bytes method, so this was repurposed to keep guarding the str/bytes surface boundary.)
def main() -> None:
    b: bytes = b"abc"
    print(b.encode())
